<item>
            <title>[LU-18169] Better support memcg for new kernels</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18169</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;EXA performance test script hanged on SLES15sp3 on NUMA system.&lt;br/&gt;
Found that once we disabled unstable_check, the test can pass.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
lctl set_param llite.*.unstable_stats=0 # disable unstable check
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally found the root reason: we are using NR_UNSTABLE_NFS wrongly, it was deprecated (DO NOT USE) on the SLES15sp3:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
NR_UNSTABLE_NFS,&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* NFS unstable pages - DEPRECATED DO NOT USE */&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Moreover, the cgroups (memcg) does not work for the newer kernel,&lt;br/&gt;
the reason is that NR_UNSTABLE_NFS was removed, and it is wrongly&lt;br/&gt;
using NR_ZONE_WRITE_PENDING for memory accounting.&lt;br/&gt;
According to the kernel patch:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;mm/writeback: discard NR_UNSTABLE_NFS, use NR_WRITEBACK instead&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
kernel v5.8-rc1 commit: 8d92890bd6b8502d6aee4b37430ae6444ade7a8c
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it should account unstable pages in NR_WRITEBACK and WB_WRITEBACK.&lt;br/&gt;
We should fix these accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
